    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "It cannot be implemented on `l2geth` because geth does not support this kind of snapshotting logic. It can be done if we used ethereumjs-vm and patched it for the OVM (we used to do that), but this is cumbersome to maintain and is not currently a priority. If anybody ends up building an OVM patch on top of the latest ethereumjs-vm, that'd be useful. Here's where we'd landed before: https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/ethereumjs-vm",
